      "Ah sorry, you're right.\r\nI guess the `r.literal` solution doesn't actually work because of https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/4613 though?\r\n\r\nYou could use `replace`, which is like `update` but without the `merge` and do the `merge` manually again as you did originally:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.db('test')\r\n .table('Session')\r\n .get('c5ce22e2-3587-4841-b9a5-bd4520de8deb')\r\n .replace(function (source) {\r\n  return r.branch(\r\n    source.hasFields('flash'),\r\n    r.branch(\r\n      source('flash').hasFields('emptyFlash'),\r\n      source.merge({ flash: r.literal({}) }),\r\n      source.merge({ flash: { emptyFlash: true } })\r\n    ),\r\n    source.merge({ flash: r.literal({}) })\r\n  );\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat should allow `r.literal` to work, because it's then directly passed into `merge`."
